page.title: 10CLUTTON'S AVENUE OF TREES
page.content: ROAD The avenue runs from the left right Upper Bristol Road to the HC HC Church. The trees were HC Hstump planted either side of the HC S path which people used to HC HC to walk along to go to S S Church. The trees used were S Sstump left over when Greyfield S HC Wood was planted over 100 S S years ago on the Warwick S HC estate. There is a mixture S S of trees- horse chestnut(HC CHURCH and sycamores(S). Two of them are cut down with the stumps remaining. One of the sycamores is dead but has not been cut down.The seats have now gone and only the bottom part of the lamp is left. Cows normally graze in the field.The height of the tallest horse chestnut is 53 metres and the tallest sycamore is 51 metres.
